<p><a name="1.6.1"><b>1.6.1 What is on the Service Pack&nbsp;6 CD </b></a></p>
<p>The \Support and \ValueAdd folders on this CD contain additional Windows components that can be installed as you need them. These files are not part of the Service Pack 6 installation, but are included for installation and use at your discretion. They include:</p>
<ul>
<li> Internet Explorer&nbsp;5</li>
<li> Microsoft Security Configuration Editor</li>
<li> Files for debugging the Service Pack</li>
<li> Fixes for Internet Mail Server&nbsp;2.0</li>
<li> DCOM, Winsock, and MSMQ files for Windows&nbsp;95 and Windows&nbsp;98</li>
<li> Updates to the MSMQ&nbsp;1.0 database for Windows&nbsp;NT&nbsp;4.0</li>
<li> Tools and instructions for OEM preinstallation of SP6</li>
<li> Files to install Routing and Remote Access Service (RRAS) in unattended Setup mode</li>
<li> Additional printer files and drivers</li>
<li> Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) files for Windows for Workgroups</li>
<li> Files required for installing a new copy of Windows&nbsp;NT&nbsp;4.0</li>
<li>Microsoft Certificate Server</li>
<li>Updates to Microsoft Internet Authentication Service (IAS)</li>
<li>A Package Definition File (PDF) for installing SP6 with Microsoft Systems Management Server (SMS)</li>
</ul>

<p>This CD also contain files in the \Alpha and \i386 folders that are not installed automatically. They are also not in the downloaded version of SP6. The files are used to install:</p>
<ul>
<li>RAS from the Service Pack CD on computers running Windows&nbsp;CE</li>
<li>Sound Blaster Plug and Play (PnP) files</li>
<li>Updated files for debugging</li>
<li>Multimedia setup files</li>
<li>Updated printer files and drivers</li>
</ul>


